abstract: There was much excitement yesterday and last night at St. Stephens, New-Brunswick, opposite this city. abstract: A GREAT BLUNDER OR A SHREWD TRICK--THE NEW JERSEY CITY POLICE LAW A DEAD LETTER.--The discovery was made, yesterday afternoon, that the new Police Law for Jersey City, creating a Board of Commissioners, was a dead letter, through informality. The City Clerk, Mr. SCOTT, sent to Trenton for a certified copy of the Police Bill, and upon looking it over, discovered that some of the Senate amendments were not contained therein.

abstract: Paper pipes possess great advantages over others for many purposes. They are highly glazed inside, and thus diminish firetion, are impregnated with bitumen, and therefore not attacked by insects or asides. Besides these points of superiority, they are sufilcieutly elastic to permit water to freeze in them without bursting, and pipes of 3, 4, and 5 inches diameter and a half inch thickness, have withstood a pressure of 500 pounds to the square inch.

abstract: Dispatches, dated March 23, received to-day from Mazatian, state that the French army, 1,100 strong, reinforced from Tepic, attacked Gens. CORONA and RUBY, three miles from Mazatlan. abstract: As was announced by yesterday morning's TIMES, the National Steam Navigation Company's steamship Virginia arrived at Quarantine on Wednesday evening, with 14 cabin and 1,029 steerage passengers, and with Aslatic cholera on board. abstract: GERMAN OPERA.--"La Dame Blanche" was given here last evening in a very effective and satisfactory manner. the audience--like the popularity of the opera--was "wide spread." It was inadequate to the occasion, and teaches us that opera, after all, is but a fashion with the masses, not a social necessity. There are but few serio-comic operas in the world, and this is one of the best.

abstract: Mr. GROVER was rewarded last evening with a fine and fashionable audience. The opera--as we here previously announced--was "Fidelio." To speak of this work in any terms of criticism or praise would be presumptious. It has taken the highest place in music, and rightly or wrongly is accepted is the culmination of all that is great in emotion or mind. The story is certainly interesting, and the music old fashioned, but beautiful.
